        principle: "Yeh **chromatography** ke siddhant par kaam karta hai, jahan components ko do phases ke beech unke partition (vitaran) ke aadhar par alag kiya jaata hai:\n1.  **Mobile Phase:** Ek inert **carrier gas** (jaise Helium, Nitrogen, ya Hydrogen) jo lagatar ek column se behta rehta hai.\n2.  **Stationary Phase:** Ek bahut patli, non-volatile liquid ki layer jo ek lambi, coiled **capillary column** (jo ek oven ke andar rakhi hoti hai) ki deewaron par lagi hoti hai.\nSample (jaise FAMEs) ko ek garam **injection port** mein daala jaata hai, jahan woh turant gas (vaporize) ban jaata hai. Carrier gas is vaporized sample ko column mein le jaati hai. Sample ke alag-alag components, unke **boiling point** aur **stationary phase ke saath affinity (interaction)** ke aadhar par, column se alag-alag gati se guzarte hain. Jo components stationary phase ke saath kam interact karte hain ya jinka boiling point kam hota hai, ve pehle nikalte hain. Jo zyada interact karte hain, ve baad mein nikalte hain. Ek **detector** (jaise FID - Flame Ionization Detector) har component ko detect karta hai jab woh column se bahar nikalta hai, jisse ek **chromatogram** (peaks ka graph) banta hai. Har peak ka 'retention time' uski pehchan batata hai aur peak ka area uski matra batata hai.\n[Image of gas chromatography principle]",
