        id: "vortex_mixer",
        name: "Vortex Mixer",
        purpose: "To **quickly, vigorously, and thoroughly mix** liquids in **test tubes** or small flasks. It is used to dissolve reagents, make dilutions, or mix samples during reactions. It is much faster and more consistent than hand-shaking.",
        principle: "It works on a very simple mechanical principle. The instrument contains a **motor** connected to an **offset drive mechanism** (or eccentric drive). A small **rubber cup** is mounted on top of this mechanism. When the motor runs, this drive mechanism spins the rubber cup in a **rapid, small circular motion (orbital motion)**. When the user presses the bottom of a test tube onto this spinning cup, this **fast vibration** is transferred to the liquid inside the tube. This vibration creates a powerful **vortex (whirlpool)** in the liquid, which thoroughly mixes the contents of the tube in a matter of seconds.",
        imageHint: "vortex mixer lab",
